,Not Recommended,567320,30289073,Posted: 2 March,all,Dobson LuggNut,"Let me preface this by saying that yes, I do only have less than 10 minutes in the game. Now onto the problems that I had in said first 10 minutes.1st. In-Game sounds and Music volume did not sync up for me. I could turn down the music volume but the game sounds would still be unbarebly loud. Obviously thats isn't supposed to happen.2nd. None of the settings in which I could change actually did something. My FOV never changed when either increasing it or decreasing it. My sensitivity never changed when either increasing it or decreasing it. The very little graphics options available never had any effect on playability. I couldn't even change my keybindings. Nothing would save after being changed. Even after relaunching the game and reinstalling.3rd. This game cost $10(off-sale). Now i understand that this game is in Early access, I do however believe that the problems that I was having should not be happeneing even in the current game state. I have requested a refund and will be getting my money back.All that being said, I do very much enjoy these types of games(FPS 3D-Platformers) so much that I will definitely come back to this game once it has been fully released and plays like a dream. The best thing I can do now is to warn people about the current problems the game is having. I wish the best of luck to 2xMilk and his dev team and I truly hope that they can make this game as good as it looks."
,Not Recommended,567320,30783824,Posted: 27 March,all,Quirken,"Pro:-gorgeous graphicsAs it currently stands, the jump physics are driving me crazy. It's early access, so maybe that will change.I found out about this game because I was playing Seum, which is more or less the same idea, except Seum has Super Meat Boy style traps. I have 600+ deaths on Seum in 2 hours of play. It's pretty difficult (though probably easier than SMB to be fair). Both games have you jumping platform to platform at fairly high speeds and have a variety of power ups.So why do I not like VThree?Simple: jump distance. It just doesn't feel right in VThree. In Seum, I can jump over numerous platforms, having to aim and lob grenades while I do it. I miss platforms all the time and die, but more often than not, I make individual jumps, just not a string of 12 when that happens.In VThree, by the second TUTORIAL level, I was already frustrated enough with the jumping that I exited the game.You can never just hit forward and jump at the right time, because the platforms aren't spaced relative to your jump distances. The next platform seems to be some awkward distance that's not even close.So if you're imagining rapid forward movement where you hold the W key and just hit space at the right time... this game isn't it. You have to not only jump at the right time, but also finesse exactly how far forward you're going. It's fiddly and it's frustrating. I'm failing jumps not because the jump itself looks difficult or because you're moving quickly and need to string a bunch of jumps together. Even basic jumps in this game are infuriating to me.I'm all for difficult games, but something is wrong if even the tutorial is frustratingly difficult.Now, it's early access, and one of the things they're going to change between now and release is ""Finalized Controls."" If they tweak the player's move speed / jump distance a little, with the same levels, I think I'd really like this game. But for now, having to nudge backwards while mid-air (or frequently let go of forward in an attempt to slow down so that you don't vastly overshoot the next platform) is a common sort of thing, and it's just not fun for me because of that. Almost all of these sorts of games have you more or less keep a constant move speed and relatively consistent jump distances."
